      "description": "Available is a 2008 Porsche Cayman S, a mid-engine masterpiece featuring the 3.4L M97.21 flat-six engine. This unit is mated to a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering power through a limited-slip differential. The vehicle exhibits excellent mechanical health, with a proactive maintenance history including a recently replaced Air-Oil Separator (AOS) and water pump. The suspension maintains its factory-tuned kinematics, utilizing MacPherson struts and stiffened anti-roll bars for precise turn-in. Braking performance remains sharp via four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers and ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior shows the honest patina of a driver\u2019s car, the drivetrain is robust, benefiting from regular 5,000-mile interval synthetic oil changes and a documented clean bill of health regarding bore scoring. This is a mechanically honest example ready for the apex.",
